      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"riding the wave\" thing doesn't work for me. It's like... the wave just keeps crashing and it's getting louder every time. It feels less like \"noise\" and more like a fundamental glitch in the system. Like the hardware itself is broken, not just the software running on it. If the mechanism for generating these thoughts is built into my actual biology, how can I \"ride it\" if the root cause is just part of the system?",
